=Discussion=

Ty Sullberg:

"Relational meaning that human relationships are the real fuel of trust networks is relationships. 

Relationships are slow to build, and culture is slow to change, but relationships and culture are far more durable and flexible than any code you could ever write. Relational tools view human relationships as primary and tooling as secondary. Relational tools foster human connection and support sensemaking that crosses the boundaries of offline and online spaces.

Ambient meaning tech that blends into the background rather than constantly demanding the attention of users." 

(https://tysullberg.substack.com/p/collective-attention-as-a-service)


